  <p>The&nbsp;<b>Competent Communication</b>&nbsp;manual (often called the&nbsp;<i>basic manual</i>) helps you to develop the basic skills that you need to prepare and present an effective speech.</p>
<p><b>1. The Ice Breaker</b><br>
For your first speech project, you will introduce yourself to your fellow club members and give them some information about your background, interests, and ambitions. Practice giving your speech to friends or family members, and strive to make eye contact with some of your audience. You may use notes during your speech if you wish. Read the entire project before preparing your talk.</p>
